The host overwrites RDI, the first argument, with `gpa`, and runs the guest again. BUT this should be OK because the value of `mem` will not have changed. This will NOT affect `mem`.

I need to confirm if `vcpu_args_set` overwrites any other registers. But in short, resetting RDI doesn't affect `mem`, because of callee-saved registers. I see there is a bug here, however, because `guest_read` calls `vcpu_args_set` twice. I would like to check if resetting any other registers can cause an issue.


